<?xml version="1.0"?>

<html metal:use-macro="sitemacros/macros/ecomap">

	<div metal:fill-slot="content" id="content">
		
		<div id="breadcrumbbar">
			<tal:block condition="login_name">
        		<span class="here">You are Here: </span><a href="/course/">My Courses</a> &gt; About
			</tal:block>
			<tal:block condition="not:login_name">
        		<span class="here">You are Here: </span><a href="/">Home</a> &gt; Help
			</tal:block>
		</div>
		
		<metal:block define-macro="message">
			<div tal:condition="message" tal:content="message" class="message" />
		</metal:block>
		
		<div id="container">
			
			<h2>
				Help
			</h2>
			
			<div id="text">
			    
				<h3>
				About the Help Section
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				This page is provided to assist you in using the
				Community Map tool as part of the Hope-NY project. The Community Map tool helps
				you prepare for unforeseen events by charting the people, groups, and resources
				available to you in times of crisis. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
				Follow these instructions for accessing, creating, and using
				the Community Map tool. 
				</p>
				
				<h3>
				Technical Requirements
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				To use the online Community Map tool, you will need the
				following: 
				</p>
				
				<ul>
				<li>Access to a Macintosh or PC computer</li>
				<li>Access to the internet through a web browser
					<ul>
					<li>PC browsers: Internet Explorer 6, Firefox 1.5</li>
					<li>Mac browsers: Safari, Firefox 1.5</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>Adobe Flash Player, which can be downloaded for free from here</li>
				<li>A minimum of 800x600 screen resolution</li> 
				<li>Javascript enabled</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h3>
				Account Help
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				Should you need technical assistance using the Community
				Map, contact the CCNMTL at
				<b>(212) 854-9058</b> and <a href="mailto:ccnmtl@columbia.edu">ccnmtl@columbia.edu</a>.
				</p>
				
				<h3>
				Logging into the Community Map Tool
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				Click the second "Click here" link on the page to login. 
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image003.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Entering Your User Name and Password
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				You will need to log in with your User Name and Password, which were provided to you during the Hope-NY training. 
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image005.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Creating a Community Map
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				Once you have logged in, you can create a map. Click the "Click here" link to create a map.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image007.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Customizing Your Community Map
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				The new Community Map you create is a blank canvas to use
				in customizing your map.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				You can change the description by clicking on the text Enter Description
				here and replacing it with your description. There will be a box around
				the description to let you know you are editing it.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To change the subject name, click on the text Enter Subject Name Here and replace
				it the same way.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image009.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<p>
				To add a person, group, or resource to the map, click and
				drag a support level icon from the
				step 1 area to a location on the map and release the mouse button. You can
				change the position of the person by dragging the person to another location.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				You can add multiple support types to a person. To add a support type, click and
				drag the letter icon next to the support type you wish to add and drop it on
				the person. If you are having trouble, you may need to drop it near the
				middle of the person box.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To delete a person, drag the person to the Trash icon.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image011.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Working with Levels and Types of Support
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				To custom name a support level (Step 1), click in the
				support level box and type the name of the person, group, or resource. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To remove a support type (Step 2) from a person or
				resource you added, click and drag the letter icon from the person to an
				empty area of the map. The other support type icons will rearrange
				themselves.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To change the support level of a person, move the mouse
				over the left side of the person box. Icons for the other levels will appear.
				Click on the icon of the level you want.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image013.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Saving Your Community Map
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				You can save your map at any time by clicking the
				Save Changes button. You will see a message at the top of your
				map indicating that your changes have been saved.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To return to your list of maps, click the &lt;&lt;
				Back to List button. If you haven't saved your changes, you will be
				prompted to save or discard your changes.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image015.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Printing Your Community Map
				</h3>
				
				<p>
				The community map you create can be printed in color or
				black and white, depending on your printer settings. For best results, make
				sure to print the map in landscape layout rather than page layout. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To print the map, click the print icon on the map page and
				follow the instructions in the print dialog box.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image017.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
				<h3>
				Managing Your Existing Community Map(s)
				</h3>
				
				
				<p>
				You may create as many maps as you like. Note that you
				will see only maps you create. You will not see other people's maps, and they
				will not see your maps. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To view a map you have created, click on the Subject Name.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				If you have already created a map, click the Create
				New button in the upper right of the page.
				</p>
				
				<p>
				To delete a map, click the checkbox next to the map or
				maps you wish to delete and click the Delete Selected button. You
				will be warned that your map(s) will be deleted.
				</p>
				
				<div align="center">
				<img class="help" src="images/help/image019.jpg" border="0" />
				</div>
				
			    
			</div>
			
		</div>
		
	</div>
	
</html>
